---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CLIF Consortium - FAQ"
  description="Frequently asked questions about the Common Longitudinal ICU data Format (CLIF), including comparisons with other data models and how to get involved."
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- Page Title -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Learn more about CLIF, how it compares to other data models, and how your institution can participate in advancing critical care research.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Content -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      
      <!-- Why CLIF over OMOP -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">Why choose CLIF over OMOP?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          CLIF is specifically designed for ICU research, capturing the granular, time-sensitive data unique to critical care settings. 
          While OMOP serves well for general clinical research, CLIF's schema reflects the actual workflows and data patterns of 
          intensive care units, including detailed ventilator parameters, vasoactive drug titrations, and other ICU-specific interventions 
          that are essential for critical care research.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CLIF vs Epic Cosmos -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">How does CLIF compare to Epic Cosmos?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          CLIF is an open-source, federated solution that keeps data at each institution. This provides complete transparency 
          in data definitions and allows institutions to maintain full control over their data while participating in 
          multi-center research. The open-source nature ensures that all researchers can understand, validate, and contribute 
          to the data model's evolution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Data Granularity -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">What level of data granularity does CLIF support?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          CLIF captures detailed ICU data including ventilator settings throughout the stay (FiO2, PEEP changes), 
          vasoactive drug titrations, and other critical parameters. While the schema supports high-frequency data, 
          current federated analyses focus on clinically meaningful time intervals that balance detail with 
          practical research needs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Join CLIF -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">How can my institution join CLIF?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We welcome new collaborators! The CLIF consortium is actively growing, with 18 institutions already participating 
          and 10 sites contributing data. To join:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li>Contact us at <a href="mailto:clif_consortium@uchicago.edu" class="text-clif-burgundy hover:text-clif-burgundy-dark underline">clif_consortium@uchicago.edu</a></li>
          <li>We'll schedule a call to discuss your institution's needs and capabilities</li>
          <li>Our team will guide you through the implementation process</li>
          <li>Join our collaborative research network</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Projects -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">I have a research project idea using CLIF. Who should I contact?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We're excited to support innovative critical care research projects! Please email us at 
          <a href="mailto:clif_consortium@uchicago.edu" class="text-clif-burgundy hover:text-clif-burgundy-dark underline">clif_consortium@uchicago.edu</a> 
          with a brief description of your project. Our scientific committee reviews proposals and can help connect you 
          with participating sites and resources.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact Section -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-clif-burgundy/5 to-clif-burgundy/10 rounded-xl p-8 border border-clif-burgundy/20 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">Have More Questions?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
          We're here to help! Whether you're interested in implementing CLIF, proposing research, or learning more about our consortium, 
          don't hesitate to reach out.
        </p>
        <a 
          href="mailto:clif_consortium@uchicago.edu" 
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-clif-burgundy text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-clif-burgundy-dark transition-colors"
        >
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
          </svg>
          Email Us
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>